WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.351 --> 00:00:11.317
Previously on AMC's
"Better Call Saul"...

2
00:00:11.328 --> 00:00:13.621
You. as the lawyer who brought
this case to the firm...

3
00:00:13.632 --> 00:00:16.257
- we can guarantee you 20%.
- That will work.

4
00:00:16.268 --> 00:00:17.778
My brother is sick!

5
00:00:17.789 --> 00:00:19.255
Unfortunately. we have an
issue we need to discuss.

6
00:00:19.257 --> 00:00:20.857
It concerns your malpractice insurance.

7
00:00:20.859 --> 00:00:22.815
I looked at the numbers.
and I can carry us.

8
00:00:22.826 --> 00:00:25.244
I'll take care of my half.
You take care of yours.

9
00:00:25.255 --> 00:00:27.279
Mr. Gatwood? Hi. Kim Wexler.

10
00:00:27.295 --> 00:00:28.628
I've got no choice.

11
00:00:28.630 --> 00:00:30.699
Hector wants to use my dad's business.

12
00:00:30.710 --> 00:00:32.676
I've got cash I can't spend.

13
00:00:32.687 --> 00:00:35.602
You opened this place to
solve a similar problem.

14
00:00:35.604 --> 00:00:37.296
Perhaps there is a way.

15
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:45.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

16
00:00:53.951 --> 00:00:56.005
_

17
00:01:16.506 --> 00:01:19.398
Mrs. Landry. you're
looking lovely as ever.

18
00:01:19.409 --> 00:01:21.359
Jimmy McGill!

19
00:01:21.370 --> 00:01:23.335
W-What are you doing here?

20
00:01:23.346 --> 00:01:25.296
Oh. I was in the area. and I thought...

21
00:01:25.307 --> 00:01:28.174
I wonder how my favorite
former client is doing?

22
00:01:28.185 --> 00:01:29.682
And I have cookies.

23
00:01:29.706 --> 00:01:31.239
Oh. you're so sweet.

24
00:01:31.241 --> 00:01:32.673
Come on in!

25
00:01:32.675 --> 00:01:33.784
After I made these.

26
00:01:33.795 --> 00:01:36.410
I looked down. and I thought. "Wow!

27
00:01:36.412 --> 00:01:38.733
That looks just like your Felix."

28
00:01:39.810 --> 00:01:41.600
They do!

29
00:01:41.611 --> 00:01:43.721
You're so thoughtful.

30
00:01:43.732 --> 00:01:45.453
I was afraid you wouldn't be here.

31
00:01:45.455 --> 00:01:46.627
Thought. with that settlement money.

32
00:01:46.638 --> 00:01:49.390
you might've moved somewhere swankier.

33
00:01:49.392 --> 00:01:52.319
- What do you mean?
- The settlement.

34
00:01:52.330 --> 00:01:54.296
The Sandpiper case?

35
00:01:54.307 --> 00:01:55.863
Now. that's gotta be
wrapped up by now. right?

36
00:01:55.865 --> 00:02:00.139
Oh. that? That... that...
that... that's still years away.

37
00:02:00.150 --> 00:02:01.202
You haven't settled yet?

38
00:02:01.204 --> 00:02:03.871
No. I don't know all the
details yet. but Erin...

39
00:02:03.873 --> 00:02:07.708
uh. Erin Brill of Davis
& Main... do you know her?

40
00:02:07.719 --> 00:02:12.471
Lovely girl. She reminds
me of a young Mary Martin.

41
00:02:12.482 --> 00:02:14.991
Oh. yes. I-I have met her.

42
00:02:15.002 --> 00:02:17.877
It's a... She's a
wonderful young lady. Uh...

43
00:02:17.888 --> 00:02:19.451
Well. she takes care of all of that.

44
00:02:19.462 --> 00:02:22.557
and she said there's
still a long way to go.

45
00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:25.256
But you've... received an offer. right?

46
00:02:25.267 --> 00:02:28.097
Something sent to you in writing?

47
00:02:28.108 --> 00:02:30.998
I mean. something more than
just Erin and you chatting?

48
00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:32.350
Oh.

49
00:02:35.701 --> 00:02:38.800
It's probably all here in this box.

50
00:02:38.811 --> 00:02:41.309
I can't make heads or tails of it.

51
00:02:41.311 --> 00:02:43.894
but you are welcome to look.

52
00:02:43.905 --> 00:02:45.304
You sure?

53
00:02:45.315 --> 00:02:47.745
Of course. It's you.

54
00:02:49.370 --> 00:02:52.875
Well. uh. I gotta say...

55
00:02:52.886 --> 00:02:56.524
I can't blame you for getting
mixed up with all this.

56
00:02:58.011 --> 00:02:59.643
I mean. these legal notices...

57
00:02:59.654 --> 00:03:02.830
I mean. no one really understands them.

58
00:03:02.832 --> 00:03:05.666
You know. I've got a law degree.

59
00:03:05.668 --> 00:03:08.002
And sometimes I can't even. uh...

60
00:03:11.780 --> 00:03:13.803
I can't even. uh...

61
00:03:19.608 --> 00:03:21.482
You haven't. uh...

62
00:03:22.061 --> 00:03:23.718
accepted this?

63
00:03:23.720 --> 00:03:25.991
Erin says we should wait.

64
00:03:26.920 --> 00:03:28.155
But...

65
00:03:30.163 --> 00:03:32.545
Erin doesn't really matter. does she?

66
00:03:32.556 --> 00:03:35.639
I mean. you're the Class Representative.

67
00:03:36.132 --> 00:03:37.565
That's a big deal.

68
00:03:37.567 --> 00:03:40.501
That means you and you alone decide.

69
00:03:40.503 --> 00:03:43.131
You're... you are the legal stand-in

70
00:03:43.142 --> 00:03:45.473
for your friends and neighbors.

71
00:03:45.475 --> 00:03:47.692
I-I don't know about all that. Jimmy.

72
00:03:47.703 --> 00:03:50.993
I-I just leave it all
to the professionals.

73
00:03:51.004 --> 00:03:52.790
Yeah. sure. sure.

74
00:03:52.801 --> 00:03:54.746
Lawyers know best. but...

75
00:03:55.434 --> 00:03:57.385
I'm sorry.

76
00:03:57.387 --> 00:03:58.719
If you won the lottery.

77
00:03:58.721 --> 00:04:00.588
I mean. you'd take the lump sum. right?

78
00:04:00.590 --> 00:04:03.257
I mean. money now is
better than money later.

79
00:04:03.259 --> 00:04:05.917
- Bird in the hand!
- I suppose.

80
00:04:05.928 --> 00:04:07.995
The more time to enjoy it!

81
00:04:09.432 --> 00:04:11.666
You really should talk to Erin.

82
00:04:11.668 --> 00:04:13.901
She knows all the ins and outs.

83
00:04:13.903 --> 00:04:15.569
Ins and outs.

84
00:04:15.571 --> 00:04:18.684
Yeah. Erin sure knows those.

85
00:04:18.695 --> 00:04:22.478
I'll be happy to talk to Erin. uh...

86
00:04:22.489 --> 00:04:24.378
Just... I just can't help but wonder

87
00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:28.192
if she's taking every aspect into a...

88
00:04:28.620 --> 00:04:30.235
Oh. Jimmy.

89
00:04:30.246 --> 00:04:32.290
I completely forgot...

90
00:04:32.301 --> 00:04:34.722
I'm on my way to chair yoga.

91
00:04:34.724 --> 00:04:36.057
I'm so sorry.

92
00:04:36.059 --> 00:04:37.425
No. it's okay.

93
00:04:37.427 --> 00:04:40.227
Um. I probably should be going.

94
00:04:40.229 --> 00:04:42.603
I have a lot to do.

95
00:04:46.535 --> 00:04:47.728
Hi.

96
00:04:47.739 --> 00:04:48.790
- Jimmy!
- Jimmy!

97
00:04:48.801 --> 00:04:51.720
- Jimmy!
- Rose. Myrtle. Helen.

98
00:04:52.105 --> 00:04:54.636
That chair yoga really works. huh?

99
00:04:54.652 --> 00:04:55.817
You all look 10 years younger.

100
00:04:55.828 --> 00:04:56.910
Oh!

101
00:04:56.921 --> 00:04:58.713
- You honeydripper.
- Hey. hurry up.

102
00:04:58.715 --> 00:04:59.947
It starts in five minutes.

103
00:04:59.949 --> 00:05:01.035
Do you want to come with us?

104
00:05:01.046 --> 00:05:02.917
You're welcome to. We can have guests.

105
00:05:02.919 --> 00:05:06.387
I would love to. uh. but
I'm not dressed for it.

106
00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:08.891
So I'll take a rain check.

107
00:05:08.902 --> 00:05:10.008
Certainly.

108
00:05:10.019 --> 00:05:11.370
Thanks for the cookies. Jimmy.

109
00:05:11.381 --> 00:05:13.394
- Bye. Jimmy! Good to see ya.
- Bye!

110
00:05:18.067 --> 00:05:19.567
That can't be right.

111
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:21.435
Can't be right.

112
00:05:25.649 --> 00:05:28.907
17.4 total.

113
00:05:29.532 --> 00:05:31.368
33% is the common fund.

114
00:05:31.379 --> 00:05:34.603
So. on 1/15.

115
00:05:34.614 --> 00:05:37.087
15 into 17...

116
00:05:38.353 --> 00:05:40.212
carry the 2.

117
00:05:40.860 --> 00:05:43.595
One million. one hundred and sixty...

118
00:05:45.181 --> 00:05:50.337
One million. one hundred
and sixty thousand!

119
00:05:51.887 --> 00:05:53.567
Holy shit!

120
00:05:58.596 --> 00:06:03.909
<font color="#007700">Synced and corrected by Aaronnmb</font>
www.addic7ed.com

121
00:06:29.221 --> 00:06:30.954
- Mr. Ehrmantraut?
- Yeah.

122
00:06:30.956 --> 00:06:32.114
Sorry to keep you waiting.

123
00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:34.388
It'll be right this way.

124
00:06:34.739 --> 00:06:37.393
Can I get you anything to
drink? Tea. water. espresso?

125
00:06:37.395 --> 00:06:39.403
No. I'm fine. Thank you.

126
00:06:55.753 --> 00:06:57.046
Ms. Rodarte-Quayle?

127
00:06:57.048 --> 00:06:59.050
- I have your next...
- Yes. thank you.

128
00:06:59.061 --> 00:07:01.276
Mr. Ehrmantraut. Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

129
00:07:01.287 --> 00:07:04.026
- Mike.
- Thanks. Justin.

130
00:07:04.037 --> 00:07:07.878
Have a seat. um... Mike.

131
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:10.143
HR sent up your start paperwork.

132
00:07:10.154 --> 00:07:12.855
I-9. W-2. Pretty standard.

133
00:07:15.066 --> 00:07:18.568
Could I have your driver's
license and Social Security card?

134
00:07:18.570 --> 00:07:19.721
Why?

135
00:07:19.732 --> 00:07:21.783
My assistant needs to make a copy.

136
00:07:22.768 --> 00:07:26.733
How does this "hire" work.
exactly? Walk me through it.

137
00:07:26.744 --> 00:07:28.678
You'll receive a paycheck from Madrigal

138
00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:30.680
in the amount of $10.000 per week.

139
00:07:30.682 --> 00:07:32.033
I believe at that rate.

140
00:07:32.044 --> 00:07:35.330
your "employment" should be
paid out in about 20 weeks.

141
00:07:35.341 --> 00:07:39.085
Mr. Fring has arranged to
cover FICA. Social Security...

142
00:07:39.096 --> 00:07:41.243
the entirety of the tax burden.

143
00:07:41.254 --> 00:07:43.555
I assume that's all right with you?

144
00:07:45.877 --> 00:07:47.330
Good. So. to that end.

145
00:07:47.332 --> 00:07:49.909
I have you down as a
"logistics consultant."

146
00:07:49.920 --> 00:07:51.655
What is that?

147
00:07:51.666 --> 00:07:55.186
It's a person who consults on logistics.

148
00:07:55.197 --> 00:07:56.791
Does it matter?

149
00:07:57.627 --> 00:08:00.510
I'm not long on logistics.

150
00:08:00.512 --> 00:08:02.385
"Security consultant" would be better.

151
00:08:02.396 --> 00:08:04.471
I used to be a cop.

152
00:08:04.482 --> 00:08:06.716
That will look better
on your "work history"

153
00:08:06.718 --> 00:08:09.112
than your current employer. SMQ Parking.

154
00:08:09.123 --> 00:08:11.948
So. you take my money.

155
00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:14.515
you run it through this
joint. and it comes out clean.

156
00:08:14.526 --> 00:08:16.159
- That it?
- Yes.

157
00:08:16.799 --> 00:08:18.799
Who knows this operation?

158
00:08:18.810 --> 00:08:20.955
You... anyone else?

159
00:08:20.966 --> 00:08:23.221
- No.
- You sure?

160
00:08:24.315 --> 00:08:28.204
May I ask. what precisely
is your concern here?

161
00:08:28.206 --> 00:08:29.987
I am concerned about what happens

162
00:08:29.998 --> 00:08:33.176
if you put my real name in your books.

163
00:08:33.643 --> 00:08:36.329
Your Madrigal is a German company.

164
00:08:36.340 --> 00:08:39.875
One thing I know about Germans
is they love a good audit.

165
00:08:41.643 --> 00:08:45.159
I oversee eight freight terminals
across Texas and the Southwest.

166
00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:48.109
Operating costs range between $800.000

167
00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:50.684
and a million dollars per week.

168
00:08:50.695 --> 00:08:54.374
All due respect. Mike. but your money?

169
00:08:54.385 --> 00:08:56.085
It's a rounding error.

170
00:08:56.096 --> 00:08:58.577
If the IRS or anyone else looks.

171
00:08:58.588 --> 00:09:00.534
you're a contractor for a
multinational corporation

172
00:09:00.545 --> 00:09:03.968
with 114.000 employees worldwide.

173
00:09:03.979 --> 00:09:06.409
You're like every other
person in this building.

174
00:09:06.411 --> 00:09:08.135
Like you?

175
00:09:09.580 --> 00:09:11.784
You think I'm not on the books?

176
00:09:11.795 --> 00:09:14.616
I am. Under my own name.

177
00:09:14.627 --> 00:09:17.587
- This the way you handled it before?
- Handled what?

178
00:09:17.589 --> 00:09:20.723
The money. For Fring's other guys.

179
00:09:21.568 --> 00:09:23.235
Other guys?

180
00:09:24.182 --> 00:09:26.699
This is the first time I've done this...

181
00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:28.010
for anyone.

182
00:09:29.346 --> 00:09:31.952
I don't know what you do. but...

183
00:09:31.963 --> 00:09:34.971
Mr. Fring must think
you're quite good at it.

184
00:09:50.612 --> 00:09:52.288
20 weeks?

185
00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:54.223
The sooner you're off
my books. the better.

186
00:09:54.225 --> 00:09:55.807
Justin?

187
00:10:03.454 --> 00:10:06.048
Can you make a copy of
these. please? Thank you.

188
00:10:11.319 --> 00:10:12.766
What?

189
00:10:14.940 --> 00:10:17.345
This is a very nice office.

190
00:10:17.816 --> 00:10:19.290
Thank you.

191
00:10:22.454 --> 00:10:25.796
Seem to be risking a
lot for a drug dealer.

192
00:10:25.807 --> 00:10:27.420
"Drug dealer"?

193
00:10:31.463 --> 00:10:34.197
If that's all you think he is...

194
00:10:34.964 --> 00:10:37.537
then you don't know Gustavo Fring.

195
00:10:56.810 --> 00:10:59.021
Let me understand you...

196
00:10:59.023 --> 00:11:01.112
you're proposing to double our premiums

197
00:11:01.123 --> 00:11:04.360
on every one of our
practicing attorneys?

198
00:11:05.003 --> 00:11:06.629
We know this is abrupt...

199
00:11:06.631 --> 00:11:08.865
new issues have come to light.

200
00:11:08.867 --> 00:11:10.742
"New issues"?

201
00:11:10.753 --> 00:11:13.124
You mean Mr. McGill's
testimony at the Bar?

202
00:11:13.135 --> 00:11:14.670
That's a part of it. yes.

203
00:11:14.672 --> 00:11:16.960
After 25 years of paying full premiums.

204
00:11:16.971 --> 00:11:19.023
I can count on one hand
the number of our claims.

205
00:11:19.034 --> 00:11:21.038
This is an underwriting
decision... that's all.

206
00:11:21.049 --> 00:11:22.645
You shouldn't take it personally.

207
00:11:22.647 --> 00:11:24.347
In some special circumstances.

208
00:11:24.349 --> 00:11:26.149
we have been known to extend a rider.

209
00:11:26.151 --> 00:11:27.383
What kind of rider?

210
00:11:27.385 --> 00:11:29.252
A senior. management-level partner

211
00:11:29.254 --> 00:11:31.254
who would supervise Charles' work.

212
00:11:31.256 --> 00:11:33.869
attend court and client
meetings with him.

213
00:11:33.880 --> 00:11:35.180
review filings.

214
00:11:35.191 --> 00:11:36.324
The few times we've done this.

215
00:11:36.335 --> 00:11:37.980
it's been for clients
with a high probability

216
00:11:37.991 --> 00:11:40.246
of catastrophic health
failure as a precaution.

217
00:11:40.257 --> 00:11:42.840
What you're saying is that
for any case Charles takes on.

218
00:11:42.851 --> 00:11:45.035
another partner would
be tied up. as well.

219
00:11:45.046 --> 00:11:46.446
and we don't bill a penny more?

220
00:11:46.457 --> 00:11:48.228
This is ludicrous.

221
00:11:48.239 --> 00:11:50.868
The insurance industry
is heavily regulated.

222
00:11:50.879 --> 00:11:52.426
I can think of a dozen infractions

223
00:11:52.437 --> 00:11:54.769
- right here off the top of my head.
- Mr. McGill...

224
00:11:54.778 --> 00:11:57.379
You're hoping we'll
either find another carrier

225
00:11:57.381 --> 00:11:59.212
or cut you an enormous check.

226
00:11:59.223 --> 00:12:00.423
Win-win for you!

227
00:12:00.434 --> 00:12:02.617
I assure you. neither
is going to happen.

228
00:12:02.619 --> 00:12:04.447
What will happen is very simple...

229
00:12:04.458 --> 00:12:06.009
you're going to do right by us

230
00:12:06.020 --> 00:12:07.755
or we will compel you to do so.

231
00:12:07.766 --> 00:12:10.358
- What do you mean by "compel"?
- You know exactly what I mean.

232
00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:13.228
If you're threatening litigation.
I'm afraid this meeting is over.

233
00:12:13.239 --> 00:12:14.849
Then it's over.

234
00:12:15.528 --> 00:12:17.176
Thank you for your time.

235
00:12:17.196 --> 00:12:19.747
Mr. Hamlin. Mr. McGill.

236
00:12:29.880 --> 00:12:31.869
All right. Where do we begin?

237
00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:34.416
Francis should start
digging into regulations.

238
00:12:34.418 --> 00:12:37.052
I'm sorry I don't have the code sections

239
00:12:37.054 --> 00:12:38.486
at my fingertips just now.

240
00:12:38.488 --> 00:12:40.288
Let's pull a team of associates

241
00:12:40.290 --> 00:12:43.488
and get them looking at every
angle of injunctive relief.

242
00:12:43.499 --> 00:12:44.843
Before close of business...

243
00:12:44.854 --> 00:12:47.228
... we're going to hit Santa
Rosa with a demand letter

244
00:12:47.230 --> 00:12:48.997
that'll make their heads spin.

245
00:12:48.999 --> 00:12:51.066
Odds are. inside a week.

246
00:12:51.068 --> 00:12:52.929
they'll be sitting at the table again.

247
00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:54.835
And if not...

248
00:12:54.838 --> 00:12:57.604
well. we've never
shied away from a fight.

249
00:13:01.465 --> 00:13:03.423
Chuck. do you remember Al McConnell?

250
00:13:03.434 --> 00:13:05.313
Of course. Helluva litigator.

251
00:13:05.315 --> 00:13:06.778
Retired now. isn't he?

252
00:13:06.789 --> 00:13:09.087
He's a professor at UNM now.

253
00:13:09.098 --> 00:13:12.087
Wrote a fantastic book on
SCOTUS during Reconstruction.

254
00:13:12.089 --> 00:13:13.321
Fascinating stuff.

255
00:13:13.323 --> 00:13:14.473
Okay...

256
00:13:14.484 --> 00:13:17.181
I was talking to him. and he mentioned

257
00:13:17.192 --> 00:13:20.134
he'd love you to come
speak to his One-Ls.

258
00:13:20.145 --> 00:13:23.215
Maybe make it a regular
thing. if you wanted.

259
00:13:24.688 --> 00:13:26.468
What are you talking about. Howard?

260
00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:28.642
What I'm saying is...

261
00:13:28.653 --> 00:13:31.506
maybe it's time to hang up your spurs.

262
00:13:32.028 --> 00:13:33.899
Become partner emeritus...

263
00:13:33.910 --> 00:13:36.478
leave your name on the firm
but focus on your legacy.

264
00:13:36.480 --> 00:13:39.915
You always said you wanted to
work on the Commerce Clause...

265
00:13:39.926 --> 00:13:41.626
you can write the book on it.

266
00:13:41.637 --> 00:13:44.471
And no longer be a practicing lawyer.

267
00:13:46.238 --> 00:13:48.892
Chuck. there's more to life than this.

268
00:13:48.903 --> 00:13:51.726
That day is far in the future. Howard.

269
00:13:51.728 --> 00:13:54.528
And I don't appreciate the suggestion.

270
00:13:56.293 --> 00:13:58.199
What if it's not a suggestion?

271
00:13:58.201 --> 00:13:59.379
Meaning?

272
00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:02.303
Meaning. if enough people
tell you that you're drunk.

273
00:14:02.305 --> 00:14:04.572
maybe it's time to sit down.

274
00:14:07.209 --> 00:14:10.588
You want me to retire
over this... insurance?!

275
00:14:10.599 --> 00:14:12.029
It's not just the insurance.

276
00:14:12.040 --> 00:14:14.874
That's the straw that
broke the camel's back.

277
00:14:16.232 --> 00:14:18.920
So this is about my condition.

278
00:14:19.202 --> 00:14:20.584
Look!

279
00:14:21.257 --> 00:14:22.584
Look!

280
00:14:24.977 --> 00:14:26.622
You see?

281
00:14:27.623 --> 00:14:29.531
See?

282
00:14:29.533 --> 00:14:31.099
I'm better!

283
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:33.904
Howard. I'm fine!

284
00:14:37.662 --> 00:14:40.167
This is not what "fine" looks like.

285
00:14:44.050 --> 00:14:46.581
Chuck. you are the best
legal mind I've ever known.

286
00:14:46.583 --> 00:14:48.183
Hands down.

287
00:14:48.803 --> 00:14:51.265
But your decision-making has become...

288
00:14:51.276 --> 00:14:52.896
unpredictable.

289
00:14:53.790 --> 00:14:57.295
And I can't be partners with
someone whose judgment I don't trust.

290
00:15:02.095 --> 00:15:03.514
Chuck...

291
00:15:17.009 --> 00:15:20.787
This right here is the
Texas-New Mexico border.

292
00:15:21.939 --> 00:15:25.975
Now. all of my wells are square...

293
00:15:25.986 --> 00:15:27.982
on the Texas side.

294
00:15:27.993 --> 00:15:31.201
When I negotiated for the
mineral and property rights.

295
00:15:31.212 --> 00:15:35.420
the surveyors said that the
next nearest pool extended to...

296
00:15:39.469 --> 00:15:41.087
about here.

297
00:15:41.098 --> 00:15:42.544
Right.

298
00:15:42.555 --> 00:15:44.766
But... after some extraction.

299
00:15:44.777 --> 00:15:47.626
the west wall of the salt dome gave way.

300
00:15:47.637 --> 00:15:50.044
opening up another pool
that extends... what...

301
00:15:50.055 --> 00:15:51.703
100 yards over the border?

302
00:15:51.705 --> 00:15:53.227
That's about the size of it. yeah.

303
00:15:53.245 --> 00:15:56.013
And now you have New Mexico
rights holders to deal with.

304
00:15:56.516 --> 00:15:58.422
You know. they should get
profit on what's theirs.

305
00:15:58.433 --> 00:16:00.422
but now I've got two
states coming after me

306
00:16:00.433 --> 00:16:02.633
for taxes on each and every gallon.

307
00:16:04.007 --> 00:16:05.985
No equipment crosses the border?

308
00:16:05.996 --> 00:16:07.595
No. ma'am.

309
00:16:07.613 --> 00:16:10.071
Nothing below the surface. like the...

310
00:16:11.157 --> 00:16:12.914
What... is it a drill bit?

311
00:16:12.916 --> 00:16:15.657
It would be the sucker rod at
this point. but no. none of that.

312
00:16:15.668 --> 00:16:17.452
Only on the Texas side.

313
00:16:17.454 --> 00:16:20.955
But that's not stopping New
Mexico from trying to bleed me.

314
00:16:21.315 --> 00:16:23.556
You said on the phone
you have a solution.

315
00:16:24.861 --> 00:16:27.259
You don't negotiate a lease
with the rights holders.

316
00:16:27.270 --> 00:16:29.839
- You offer to pay them damages.
- Damages?

317
00:16:29.850 --> 00:16:31.980
For diminishing their resource.

318
00:16:31.995 --> 00:16:35.590
A significant fraction of the
value of the New Mexico portion.

319
00:16:35.601 --> 00:16:37.808
but without paying for
the rights themselves.

320
00:16:38.208 --> 00:16:40.199
So a kind of a payoff.

321
00:16:41.409 --> 00:16:43.355
Then you don't get hit with the taxes.

322
00:16:43.366 --> 00:16:45.499
You think you can make that fly?

323
00:16:45.510 --> 00:16:48.011
If someone came to me with this offer...

324
00:16:48.022 --> 00:16:49.884
I'd sure as hell take it.

325
00:16:49.886 --> 00:16:52.353
Wish I'd called you sooner.

326
00:16:52.925 --> 00:16:54.660
Way they're makin' noise.

327
00:16:54.671 --> 00:16:57.308
if I don't get this thing wrapped
up by the end of the quarter.

328
00:16:57.319 --> 00:17:00.601
I'm pretty sure the tax
boys are gonna take me apart.

329
00:17:00.612 --> 00:17:03.113
And that's two weeks from now?

330
00:17:05.542 --> 00:17:07.068
I can do it by then.

331
00:17:07.070 --> 00:17:08.636
Really?

332
00:17:08.638 --> 00:17:10.526
If we can get all the
rights holders in one place.

333
00:17:10.537 --> 00:17:13.071
I can walk them through
what we're proposing.

334
00:17:13.082 --> 00:17:15.243
If they're smart. they'll go for it.

335
00:17:15.245 --> 00:17:16.744
Well. hot damn.

336
00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.273
Kevin said you were a miracle
worker. but I didn't believe him.

337
00:17:22.284 --> 00:17:24.085
I'm startin' to.

338
00:17:24.087 --> 00:17:27.488
Yeah. well. let me work that
miracle first. then we'll talk.

339
00:17:27.490 --> 00:17:28.923
You know the way outta here?

340
00:17:28.925 --> 00:17:32.304
I got a drillhead that's acting up on me

341
00:17:32.315 --> 00:17:34.862
out on the north forty I gotta check.

342
00:17:34.864 --> 00:17:36.330
Yeah. I'm good.

343
00:17:36.332 --> 00:17:37.695
You need anything from me.

344
00:17:37.706 --> 00:17:39.398
you got my cell. Call me.

345
00:17:39.409 --> 00:17:40.859
Will do.

346
00:18:01.425 --> 00:18:04.557
Billy Gatwood meeting
notes. Contact Gatwood Oil.

347
00:18:04.568 --> 00:18:07.909
Get names and numbers for
New Mexico rights holders...

348
00:18:12.521 --> 00:18:14.018
Shit!

349
00:19:13.796 --> 00:19:15.663
No. no. no. no!

350
00:19:15.665 --> 00:19:17.798
No. no. no! Shit!

351
00:19:42.603 --> 00:19:45.655
Continuing notes from
Gatwood Oil meeting.

352
00:19:45.666 --> 00:19:47.908
Contact rights holders.

353
00:19:47.919 --> 00:19:49.908
begin scheduling.

354
00:20:13.656 --> 00:20:15.089
Howard!

355
00:20:17.458 --> 00:20:21.495
- What are you doing here. Jimmy?
- We have business to discuss.

356
00:20:21.497 --> 00:20:23.397
Is this about Chuck?

357
00:20:23.399 --> 00:20:25.199
Who?

358
00:20:25.201 --> 00:20:27.878
If you actually have business.
then call my secretary.

359
00:20:27.889 --> 00:20:30.604
I did. She stonewalled
me. as if you didn't know.

360
00:20:30.606 --> 00:20:32.062
Sandpiper.

361
00:20:32.073 --> 00:20:34.175
- What about it?
- It's time to settle.

362
00:20:34.177 --> 00:20:35.791
I-I saw the current offer.

363
00:20:35.802 --> 00:20:38.697
The clients make their losses
back. plus a solid chunk of change.

364
00:20:39.872 --> 00:20:41.712
Not that it's any of your business.

365
00:20:41.723 --> 00:20:44.512
but we project a final number
far higher than the current offer.

366
00:20:44.523 --> 00:20:46.325
I get it. I get it. You hold out.

367
00:20:46.336 --> 00:20:48.723
maybe you squeeze a grand
more for each client.

368
00:20:48.734 --> 00:20:50.981
Meanwhile. HHM nets a few million.

369
00:20:51.005 --> 00:20:53.853
You know. you're screwing the
clients for your own benefit.

370
00:20:53.864 --> 00:20:56.864
Oh. so now you're
worried about the clients?

371
00:20:56.866 --> 00:20:58.481
It's the right thing
to do. and you know it.

372
00:20:58.492 --> 00:21:00.001
Please.

373
00:21:00.012 --> 00:21:02.870
All you care about is
your share of the payout.

374
00:21:04.063 --> 00:21:06.137
It's like talking to Gollum.

375
00:21:06.148 --> 00:21:09.041
You're transparent. And pathetic.

376
00:21:10.480 --> 00:21:12.387
You want a handout?

377
00:21:13.848 --> 00:21:14.973
Here.

378
00:21:17.053 --> 00:21:18.278
Huh?

379
00:21:19.455 --> 00:21:21.259
Next time...

380
00:21:21.270 --> 00:21:23.090
why don't you bring a tin cup?

381
00:21:23.092 --> 00:21:25.005
It'd be more honest.

382
00:21:26.496 --> 00:21:29.096
Listen. Howard. settle
this and settle it now.

383
00:21:29.098 --> 00:21:30.864
It's in everyone's best interests!

384
00:21:30.875 --> 00:21:32.933
Meaning it's in your best interests.

385
00:21:32.935 --> 00:21:34.902
And if we don't. what are you gonna do?

386
00:21:34.904 --> 00:21:36.637
Peel off some members of the class.

387
00:21:36.639 --> 00:21:38.541
leak some insider info to Schweikart?

388
00:21:38.552 --> 00:21:40.741
Oh. I doubt it. I know you're low enough

389
00:21:40.743 --> 00:21:42.610
to do something like that.
but you're too damn greedy.

390
00:21:42.612 --> 00:21:43.852
You do any of that.

391
00:21:43.863 --> 00:21:46.157
and you'll be jeopardizing your payday.

392
00:21:47.150 --> 00:21:49.299
You'll get your damn money.

393
00:21:49.310 --> 00:21:51.102
You're just gonna have to wait for it.

394
